ting surfaces (chat row menu, project row menu, pinned-rail kebab), driven by each item's `archivedAt`. Optimistic list removal + toast on archive. For now, unarchive is reachable only from the pinned rail (there is no Archived view and no open-chat unarchive control).\n- **Response types gain `archivedAt`**: `ChatResponse`, `ChatListItemResponse`, `ProjectResponse`, and the pin ref cards (`ChatRefCard`, `ProjectRefCard`) so the client can render state and the toggle.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### New Capabilities\n- `item-archive`: the archive state on chats and projects (the `archived_at` column), reversible archive/unarchive via the `PATCH` flag, overview-list exclusion with `?archived` surfacing, search unaffected, pinned-rail inclusion with indicator, the `409` mutation guard on archived items, and the web Archive⇄Unarchive toggle (pinned-rail-only unarchive for now).\n\n### Modified Capabilities\n- `projects`: the project overview list now excludes archived projects by default and surfaces them only via `?archived=true`; an archived project rejects all updates except unarchive and delete.\n\n## Impact\n\n- **Schema (apps/api, sole DB owner)**: new nullable `archived_at` timestamp on `chats` and `projects`; one drizzle-kit migration. No RLS change — `archived_at` is a plain column under the existing `chats_owner`/`projects_owner` policies (owner-scoped write, global read effect).\n- **Security / tenancy**: archive is owner-only and datastore-enforced; cross-tenant archive/unarchive is denied (no existence oracle — maps to the same 404 as any inaccessible resource). A negative test pins that User B cannot archive/rename/delete-archive User A's item, and that archived items do not leak across tenants in lists.\n- **API**: `UpdateChatDto`/`UpdateProjectDto` gain `archived`; responses + pin ref cards gain `archivedAt`; `GET /chats` and `GET /projects` gain the `?archived` filter; the message-send path and both update services gain the archived guard; `openapi.json` reg