            "content": "## Context\n\nEvery chat/project row menu and the pinned-rail kebab ship a **disabled `Archive`** item (issue #192), per the repo rule that not-yet-built controls are disabled, never dead clicks or hidden. The pinning rework (`item-pins`, design D5) just established that *pin* state is per-user and lives in its own `pins` table. Archive is the opposite axis: it is an **owner action that mutates the resource itself** and is meant to be seen by everyone. So archive is a plain `archived_at` column on `chats`/`projects`, not a per-user relation.\n\nToday a chat is single-owner, so \"archived for everyone\" means \"for the owner across all sessions.\" That is also the *future-correct* shape if multi-user viewing ever lands: the owner archives, all viewers see it gone. A per-user archive relation would be the wrong model.\n\n## Goals / Non-Goals\n\n**Goals:**\n\n- A reversible, owner-scoped `archived_at` flag on `chats` and `projects`.\n- Archive/unarchive as a `PATCH` partial update (`archived: boolean`), not an RPC verb — consistent with the filing precedent (`projectId` on `PATCH /chats`).\n- Overview lists hide archived by default; `?archived=true` surfaces them (API-reversible, UI-less for now).\n- Archived items stay in the pinned rail with an indicator, surfacing status (and a multi-user signal) rather than silently vanishing.\n- A hard guard: archived items reject every write except unarchive and delete (`409`).\n- The three existing Archive controls become Archive⇄Unarchive toggles.\n\n**Non-Goals (explicitly deferred):**\n\n- The Archived *view* (per-scope archived lists with an Unarchive action).\n- Styling of the \"Archived\" indicator (later design change).\n- UI treatment of the `409` guard (separate design change).\n- An open-chat unarchive control — unarchive is reachable only from the pinned rail in this change.\n- Unarchiving non-pinned archived items from the UI (reachable only via `?archived`/API or a future view).\n\n## Decisions\n\n### D1. `archived_at` is a column on the resource, not a per-user relation\n\nArchive is global per item; pins are per-viewer. A separate `archived` table keyed by `(user_id, item)` would be the wrong inversion and would not give the desired \"owner archives, all viewers see it gone\" semantics. A nullable timestamp column is the minimal correct shape, and it reads as a first-class state in responses.\n\n- _Alternative rejected:_ per-user `archived` relation (mirrors `pins`) — gives per-viewer archive, contradicts the global requirement, and forces a join on every list read.\n\n### D2. Reversible via `PATCH` flag + `?archived` surfacing\n\n`UpdateChatDto`/`UpdateProjectDto` gain `archived: boolean`. `true` sets `archived_at = now()`; `false` clears it; omitted leaves it unchanged. Idempotent. `GET /chats` and `GET /projects` exclude archived by default (`WHERE archived_at IS NULL`) and accept `?archived=true` to include them. No dedicated archive endpoint, no Archived view route.\n\n- _Alternative rejected:_ an RPC `POST /chats/:id/archive` verb — violates the resource-design convention the repo enforces for pin/filing; a flag on the existing partial-update is the established pattern.\n\n### D3. Overview excludes, pinned rail includes (with indicator), search untouched\n\n- Overview lists (`listChatsWithLastMessage`, `listForUser`): `WHERE archived_at IS NULL` added to the existing `.where` (the chat list already ANDs `ownerUserId` + optional `projectId`; this is one more AND term).\n- Pinned rail (`listWithCards`): **no exclusion** — archived pinned items are returned so the rail can show an \"Archived\" indicator. The pin ref cards (`ChatRefCard`/`ProjectRefCard`) gain `archivedAt` so the web can render the indicator and the Archive⇄Unarchive toggle label.\n- Search: unchanged — archived items remain searchable; this is the deliberate delete-vs-archive distinction.\n\n- _Alternative rejected:_ hiding archived from the pinned rail too — silently dropping an archived item is confusing (and, in the multi-user future, hides an owner action from other viewers). Keeping it with an indicator surfaces status.\n\n### D4. Archived items reject all writes except unarchive + delete (`409`)\n\nA single `assertMutable(resource)` helper (in the chat and project service layers) throws `409 Conflict` (\"archived; unarchive or delete first\") when `archived_at IS NOT NULL` and the operation is not an unarchive (`PATCH archived=false`) or a delete. It is called in `chats.service.updateChat`, `projects.service.updateProject`, and the **message-send path** (so sending a message into an archived chat is rejected — this *replaces* the earlier \"send un-archives\" idea, which was dropped as the wrong default). Status is `409`, not `423`, because delete is explicitly allowed, so \"locked\" would mislead.\n\n- _Alternative rejected:_ auto-unarchive on send — makes archive fragile (any reply silently undoes it) and contradicts the \"archived = set aside\" intent.\n\n### D5. Web: Archive⇄Unarchive toggle, pinned-rail-only unarchive\n\nThe three existing disabled `Archive` menu items (chat row, project row, pinned-rail kebab) become toggles. Each item carries `archivedAt` (from the list-item / pin response); the control shows **Archive** when not archived, **Unarchive** when archived. Archive does optimistic list-cache removal + toast (no navigation — the open chat \"stays active\" per the earlier decision). Unarchive re-admits the item to the overview list. A single `setArchived(itemType, itemId, archived)` mutation mirrors the pins toggle shape.\n\nBecause the overview excludes archived, an unarchived item is reachable only where it is still visible: the **pinned rail** (per D3) and, if you are on it when you archive, the still-open chat (which has no unarchive control in this change). Non-pinned archived items cannot be unarchived from the UI yet — accepted, since there is no Archived view; they remain reachable via `?archived`/API and a future view.\n\n### D6. `archivedAt` in responses and pin ref cards\n\n`ChatResponse`, `ChatListItemResponse`, `ProjectResponse`, `ChatRefCard`, `ProjectRefCard` all gain `archivedAt` (`date-time`, nullable). This is the only schema-adjacent addition beyond the column; pin state stays out of these representations (still `item-pins` D5 — archive is a different axis).\n\n## Risks / Trade-offs\n\n- **[Non-pinned archived item is un-unarchivable from UI]** → accepted for this change (no Archived view); reachable via `?archived`/API and a future view. Documented as a known limitation, not a gap.\n- **[Pinned-rail indicator has no styling yet]** → the data (`archivedAt` on ref cards) ships now; visual treatment is a separate, later design change.\n- **[409 has no UI message yet]** → API-only guard this change; the user sees a generic failure. UI handling is a separate design change. Risk is contained (archive/deletion still work; only edits to archived items are refused).\n- **[Archiving an item with an in-flight run]** → the open chat \"stays active,\" so a run in progress keeps running after archive; no block added (would be a behavior change beyond scope). Note it; add a guard only if a requirement arises.\n- **[Multi-user read-sharing not yet built]** → `archived_at` global semantics are already correct for that future; no retrofitting needed.\n\n## Migration Plan\n\n1. Schema: drizzle-kit migration adding nullable `archived_at` timestamp to `chats` and `projects` (no RLS change; column falls under existing owner policies). `drizzle-kit check` passes.\n2. DTOs + responses: add `archived` to update DTOs and `archivedAt` to responses + pin ref cards; regenerate `openapi.json`.\n3. List exclusion + surfacing: `WHERE archived_at IS NULL` in overview lists; `?archived=true` param; pinned-rail list keeps archived and returns `archivedAt` on cards.\n4. Guard: `assertMutable` in both update services + the send path → `409`.\n5. Web: toggle the three Archive controls; add `setArchived` mutation; mirror `archivedAt` in web types; optimistic remove + toast on archive.\n6. Verify: `pnpm --filter api build/test/typecheck/lint`; web `test/typecheck/lint`; RLS negative specs (cross-tenant archive/rename/delete-archive denied; archived absent from other users' lists); `openspec validate chat-project-archive` clean.\n\n## Open Questions\n\nNone blocking. Follow-ups tracked (not in this change): the Archived view + Unarchive action; indicator styling; `409` UI handling; open-chat unarchive control; unarchiving non-pinned archived items from the UI.\n",
